description:
# Task: Create Main Stylesheet

## What
Create the Sass stylesheet that extends Minima theme.

## Why
- Jekyll requires front matter to process .scss files
- Imports Minima base for consistent styling
- Provides hook for custom overrides
- Single file manages all custom CSS

## File Content
```scss
---
---

@import "minima";

// Custom overrides below
// Keep minimal for MVP - only add if default minima is insufficient
```

## Key Points
1. **Empty front matter (---)**: Required for Jekyll to process Sass
2. **@import "minima"**: Pulls in all Minima theme styles
3. **Comments**: Placeholder for future customization

## Why Minimal CSS for MVP
- Minima is already responsive and professional
- Over-customizing delays shipping
- Can iterate on design post-launch
- Each custom rule is maintenance debt

## Future Customization Examples (NOT for MVP)
```scss
// Example: Adjust primary color
// $brand-color: #2a7ae2;

// Example: Custom header styling
// .site-header { 
//   border-bottom: 2px solid $brand-color; 
// }
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] File exists at assets/css/style.scss
- [ ] Has empty front matter
- [ ] Imports minima
- [ ] Site styling works after build
- [ ] No Sass compilation errors

## Parent Epic
[EPIC] Assets & Static Files
